<plot>A couple of Quebeckers' vacation in Brazil turns into a nightmare when Raphael, their only child, gets lost in the streets. The police won't bother looking for him and even suggests visiting the local morgue. It looks at first like a simple matter of indifference. But these parents are soon to find out that there is a "silence law" under which policemen proceed to a "cleansing" of the streets by murdering homeless children, and Raphael could be next...</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?331626</url></doc>
